The paper deals with solving inverse problems in image processing using deep neural networks and optimization algorithms. The primary focus is on convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for accelerating conventional optimization algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training DNNs, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The optimization algorithms used in the paper are related to iterative methods, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves numerical analysis and optimization, which can be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper proposes a CNN to yield parameters in optimization algorithms, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
